 reading of well-known philosophical texts. The aim is to carve out a space for a new kind of relationship between anthropology and philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107042040 cprintz978080474886540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362442940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503624429423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503624429/original  a978-3-11-070420-4  Stanford University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles